{"key":"processedPost-9070203","value":{"id":9070203,"first":9069929,"last":9070359,"when":1223911320,"utime":"10/13/08 06:22 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />I had already turned the pot on low heat but the water had not started to turn into steam yet, so the PC was only on for about 5-10 mins at low heat.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Since your question was already answered, I'll mention that you should start out on <i>high heat</i>, not low.&nbsp; The idea is to boil the water.&nbsp; That will happen much faster on high.&nbsp; Reduce heat as pressure is reaching 15psi, and then regulate the stove burner to its lowest setting that will maintain pressure.&nbsp; Don't allow excessive steam to escape because it can run your PC dry, as well as dry out the moisture in your grains.<br />RR","title":"Re: wbs in the PC. Quick question","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}